			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Listen to my words, for my mouth is the Mouth of Innoruuk. </span>
<br />

<br />
It was still dark, not a spark of light to show her where she was, just shadow all around, like a thick blanket smothering her. But who and where was she? Did it matter? She was here, swimming in the blackness. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">In the time that all was dark, Veeshan, the Winged Mother, came upon this world while hunting. She saw that it was rich and promising, and would nurture her great children, and so here laid her eggs.</span> 
<br />

<br />
A slight buzzing began, slowly swelling to a roar, voices, thousands of them, raised together. A spark flared up in the distance... 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">The Creeping Coward Brell Serilis discovered her nest, and through treacherous cunning made pacts with the other gods to steal the world from the Winged Mother.</span> 
<br />

<br />
She cringed, shielding her ears from the deafening sound, her eyes squinting, trying to adjust to even the smallest light in her dark prison. The velvet blackness seemed to go on forever, as if she could walk and walk and never find the end. But that small spark slowly grew closer... 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">The gods in their council said "Let us not speak of this to Innoruuk, for He is great, but by trickery we may have what is rightfully his, as well. </span>
<br />

<br />
Eyes unused to sight began to water as the light became stronger and larger, moving towards her alarmingly. One part of her wanted to run, but to where? There was no end to her prison.. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Then the gods covered the world with their worms, and these worms crawled to all the corners of the world, and grew into the Others.</span> 
<br />

<br />
And the light became a form, and her heart burned in hatred and fear. His shape was familiar, one that she could never escape. Her god, her jailor, her tormentor... 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">But Our Father could not be deceived, nor can He be thwarted. </span>
<br />

<br />
The voice seemed to surround her, batter her with its resonance... and tear her open from the inside out. "So, Evileene, have you learned that you can naut defy me?" 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">He took for His own the first Queen and King of all the Elves from their thrones at Takish-Hiz. He led them from Tunare, the False Mother. He lifted them from their ignorance and showed them His Will. </span>
<br />

<br />
She nodded wordlessly, the defiance that still sparked in her eyes pushed down. He had already proven He would win, not she. To fight Him was foolish. "Answer me child. Have you learned to Hate? Do you remember who you are?" 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">We are their children. We are the instruments of Our Father's Will. We shall destroy the offspring of the false gods and cleanse the world of their treachery. We will deliver this world to Our Father.</span> 
<br />

<br />
She gasped, drawing great breaths of air through lungs that had not been used in ages. Her eyes blurred and teared painfully as they adjusted to her surroundings, stone walls and candles and wooden benches... tier'dal faces all around. Hands all around lifting her up, sitting her upright on the cold stone, goosebumps raising on her skin as more hands wrapped her in a rough cloth. The sensations of the physical world battered her senses... and her voice, for the first time in forever she heard it.. 
<br />

<br />
"I am born Necromancer. My hand is the Hand of Innoruuk, the Dead shall not rest in His service..." 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Strive for the Day of Darkening!</span><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
