				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Bodies crowded all around, pushing her towards a spot in the room, almost as if they were herding cattle. Soft fabrics, satins, silks, brushing against her, the sensations overwhelming after the time spent imprisoned in a world without substance. Finally, they were still. She was huddled close to several others. Rough, threadbare wool was what she felt brushing against her now, from both the garment draped around her own form, and the tier'dal she was pressed against. The smell of fear hung heavy around the group, but after so long as a tortured soul in the Father's realm, little could frighten her now. Only going back there had the power to do that... 
<br />

<br />
Her eyes gazed downward, still unfocused, still unused to their corporeal form. How long had it truly been? Sharp pains shot through her head as she fought to clear her vision. It was as if she was an infant again, learning to see. The chanting hurt her ears as well, but it was almost a welcome pain, to actually HEAR again, for the sounds to reverberate through her body and resonate around her. Even as the rough wool scratched and irritated her skin, she welcomed the feel of it, the reminder that she was alive. She took a deep breath relishing the feel of her lungs filling with air, and froze. There was a familiar scent in the air, rising above the fear and incense in this chapel.  Blood.  It soaked the stones, dyed the altar she had just been laying on.  Death.
<br />

<br />
The throng pushed her forward with the others clad in the same rough robes.  She could hear those herded with her mumbling prayers beneath their breath, their terror almost delicious to her after so long with only her own fears to feed on.  What seemed like hundreds of eyes peered at them, the slight red glow of their ultravision almost seeming to add an eerie light to the darkened church. One jaluk in a woolen robe was shoved forward and landed heavily on his knees in front of the Priest. The Priest spoke up, his voice quiet, yet carrying throughout the room. 
<br />

<br />
"Great are the Children of Innoruuk. Great is Our Father. His Will is Our Will, our strength is His Strength. May Our Father look down upon Us as We gather here, for this night He shall reclaim those children that were lost." 
<br />

<br />
The jaluk before him was lifted roughly to his feet. The Priest looked at him dispassionately, then raised his eyes to the image of the Eye of Innoruuk, magically suspended over the altar. 
<br />

<br />
"Hear me, Our Father. Consider this Child that stands before Us. They have defied You and listened to the lies of the Others, but they have returned, properly penitent, for Your Use. Allow them to plead for acceptance, for they are Your Creation, and deserve only to live in Your Servitude." 
<br />

<br />
His attention turned back to the jaluk before him. 
<br />

<br />
"Do you, Uuananyen Z'Rist, wish to submit yourself willingly to the Eye of Our Father, so that you may be found worthy to join His True Service?" 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Eve watched spellbound, finally aware of why they were all there that evening, why Innoruuk had brought her back.  She too would be expected to stand before the Priest and the Church and declare her faith and obedience to the God that had tormented her all these years, the one God she could not escape, even in death... 
<br />

<br />
"Do you admit to the superiority of the Power of Innoruuk, bow to Him as your one True Father, and swear to live and die for His Will?" Z'Rist nodded his head quietly, his eyes fixed on the Priest before him. Eve's eyes were drawn to a commotion she saw in a far corner of the room, where someone was being brought in through a small door... a fier'dal, bound and gagged, dressed in the white robes of a sacrifice. Her stomach tightened at what she guessed was about to happen. Z'Rist was still fixated on the Priest.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
