				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"Do you swear to follow and uphold the Commandments of Obedience in every thought, word, and deed?" 
<br />

<br />
Z'Rist nodded again, a slight hesitance in the movement. 
<br />

<br />
"Do you swear to serve Our Queen and King, as embodiments of the Will of Innoruuk?" 
<br />

<br />
Another silent nod. 
<br />

<br />
"Do you swear to reject the lies of love and free will taught by the Lying Gods?" 
<br />

<br />
Still unaware of the fier'dal, Z'Rist slowly nodded his head. A malicious grin spread across the Priest's mouth. He turned to look at the bound elf, dragging Z'Rist's attention to her as well. The jaluk sagged, almost dropping to his knees in horror, as he saw his wife pushed onto the sacrificial altar... 
<br />

<br />
"Bwael, then as a follower of the True God, you will have nau trouble dispatching this female that you have agreed that you do naut love?" Z'Rist was handed a dagger, and a low, evil chuckle rose in the Priest's throat.
<br />

<br />
The shadows in the church seemed more sinister than ever, and even the candlelight had a threatening aura, the cold stone walls almost seeming to breathe, as if the place itself was a living being of evil. The altar the fier'dal lay upon was cold stone, the same bloodstained surface that Eve had been laid out upon seemingly only moments ago. The floor all around it was stained with blood, the life force of countless victims of all races mixed together here. Z'Rist had eyes for nothing but the slender elf, draped in white, like a virgin sacrifice. That robe would soon be crimson with blood, he knew. Her golden eyes met his in fear and a certain kind of resignation... she knew what her fate was to be, whether at her lover's hands, or at the hands of one of these around her. If by his hand, at least he might be spared. She spoke softly, in the language of her own people, a tongue he knew well. "Do it.. now. Do not let my life end by their hands, but yours." 
<br />

<br />
Her request chilled another in the church that day as well, for she well understood that forbidden tongue. What horrors were unfolding before her eyes, here, at her rebirth. But Z'Rist knew nothing of what was in her heart, nor did he care. His only thoughts were for Ayllysa. His wife. His downfall. His end. He knew what he must do, but he could not force his arm to move, to complete the downward stroke, to drain the life from those eyes. 
<br />

<br />
The tier'dal looked at the bound wood elf, panic in his eyes. His nerveless fingers dropped the dagger he had been handed, and it fell, clattering noisily on the stone floor, though he heard not a sound. Calmly, one of those who had brought her in reached for his own dagger, cutting her open from throat to belly in one clean stroke, her keening cry echoing throughout the room. Z'Rist made a move for the guard, insane with fear and grief, and the Priest calmly thrust a dagger he had been concealing in his robes into the jaluk's heart, giving it a sharp twist, then pulling it back, the three ornate and razor sharp prongs taking the still-beating heart with them as they were removed. Z'Rist collapsed silently to the floor, the blood from his corpse mixing with that of his forbidden bride and all the other victims of this evil place. Dropping the now-still heart to the ground next to him, the Priest laughed maliciously. "You are nau follower of Innoruuk. May you serve Him better in death than you did in life." 
<br />

<br />
"Heed my words! The Father does naut lie. He tells Us from the outset what the penalty for betraying the Will is, He does naut preach false forgiveness and empty promises. He does naut lie and tell Us we have free will, and the right to choose Our Path. His Will is Our will, and we ARE His Will. To turn your back on that is a crime against Father and tier'dal. However, Innoruuk is naut without mercy to His Children. Those who are truly willing to come back into the Will shall be forgiven, and their trespasses forgotten. Those who attempt to deceive Him shall suffer the fate of this one."<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Evileene Diablerie on Wed Feb 02, 2005 2:12 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
