				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">His piercing red eyes moved over those in the congregation, settling menacingly on Eve.  A short nod of his head motioned her forward and for the first time since being reborn, she felt fear again.  Fear of being returned to the Abyss and to the domain of Hate, fear of being nothing but a soul trapped in Innoruuk's prison for all of eternity.
<br />

<br />
What the others'  tests were to be, Eve did not know. Her eyes were fixed on the priest's glowing red eyes, the malevolence in them warning her that she had an unpleasant surprise in store. She had been separated from the others, with them held securely back, watching, as she had watched Z'Rist.  Eve stared at the man in front of her, his lips twisted into an evil smile, and held back a shudder. It did not do to show fear to one such as this, the scent of blood would only whip him into more of a frenzy. His indigo skin glowed in the flickering candlelight, his face almost handsome but for the utter cruelty in every line and shadow. Although, among most of their people, that would be considered an asset. 
<br />

<br />
"Are you ready, Ilharess?" The title was spoken in a mocking tone, the former power she had wielded at odds with the helpless situation she now found herself in. Her hands curled into fists, the nails biting into her palms, to the point of drawing blood. Forget self-preservation, her pride would not let her show any fear to the arrogant bastard in front of her. 
<br />

<br />
"I am ready." Though inside she was shivering in terror of all that had gone before and what was about to happen, her voice was cold and emotionless. She shook her guards off and stood there, waiting.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">The jalil, only 50 years of age, still barely more than a child by tier'dal standards, raced to the Oasis of Marr with all the speed she could muster. A sister of her qu'ellar was in trouble, a rivvil monk tormenting her and threatening her, and there was nauthing else to be done but rush to her defense. But what could one such as she still young in the craft do? 
<br />

<br />
The rivvil stood over the terrified wizard, young Aeslin did naut have the courage or backbone most tier'dal had, and prized. But then, she was also a member of the Spurned, almost expected to be weaker, to be a burden. Evileene called upon her skeleton companion, but it was easy to see he would be little to nau help against this one. The sun was blinding to the tier'dal girls, alien and uncomfortable, and they were disoriented in the bright light. 
<br />

<br />
A brighter glare caught her eye, and she glanced over, visibly relaxing as she saw one of the elders of the qu'ellar, a warrior named Zaknyfein. His silver armor shone brilliantly in the sun, blinding the monk momentarily. The tone of Zak's voice and his hold on his weapons quickly convinced the bully he meant what he said. "You will leave my sisters alone, rivvil iblith. Or you will feel my blade. Begone, while I still have hold of my temper." 
<br />

<br />
Perhaps that was the moment she was lost, Eve reflected much later. She had always thought that the pale dream of a knight in shining armor to rescue the maiden was foolish, and the maiden was altogether too weak if she could naut save herself. But perhaps there was something to that... </span>
<br />

<br />
The tier'dal that was dragged. hands bound before him, towards the altar bore little resemblance to the brave warrior rescuer of so long ago. He had changed enough that she could have been forgiven for not knowing him, so many years and such a difference from the proud but kind tier'dal he had been. He was stooped, weak. His spirit had been broken long ago it seemed, his ivory hair yellowed and hanging lank against his shoulders. This then was her hell... her sacrifice. The man she had spoken vows to, lived with, laughed with, had a daughter with... the man she had loved, who had turned her on this path in the first place. His eyes met hers, dull and glassy, but she saw a spark of remembrance, of recognition... and then of dissappointment.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
