			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rage built up inside her, almost like a fire, an inferno of hatred. Innoruuk's emotion, Innoruuk's control. "I almost let you destroy me!" she hissed in a rage. "I was weak, pathetic, all in the name of the lie you sold me. Love!" She spit at his feet.
<br />

<br />
His pathetically stooped body straightened momentarily, his bowed head upright again in an almost sad showing of pride. Too little, too late. "I did naut destroy you Eve. They did. They did." His voice shook slightly. "And you did. The woman you were when we met.. so young, so innocent, so full of life. And Innoruuk and His teachings took that away. Slowly, so slowly you did naut even see, you became another woman. Twisted, bitter, angry. So full of Hate. But I saw. All too well I saw, I watched it. And it destroyed me too..." His blue eyes shimmered with tears, with grief over what had been, and what could have. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">The tier'dal woman looked up at her mother, ebony eyes misty with a sheen of tears. "There is nauthing left to you, Ilharess. Naut but hate, and a lust of power. You do naut need me, you need nau one. At least Father needs me. He loves me. All I hear from you is duty, your duty to Innoruuk, your duty to Neriak. What of your duty to me? To Father? You have abandoned us for your god, and to your own fears. I lost my family, but at least I tried to hold them together. At least I tried to love! You just allow Innoruuk and his teachings to twist you further every day." 
<br />

<br />
The Ilharess glanced around, worried that others may have overheard the conversation. "Zarynne! This is naut the time, daughter. We shall talk later--" 
<br />

<br />
"There will be nau later, Ilharess. Aluve." </span>
<br />

<br />
"This is who we are Zak! This is what we were created for. Innoruuk is our Father, we are His tools. It was you who lost that!" The rage was fading slowly, replaced by almost hopelessness. Memories battered her mercilessly, regrets slipped past her careful defenses, weaking her further. Centuries since she had seen him, and this was what he had become. There was no hope for anyone, no hope. She had thought he of all that she knew would break free. Would live away from this Hate. But even he... "And look at you. Just look. Give me one reason why I should naut put you out of your misery." 
<br />

<br />
"Put me out of my misery, Eve? Or out of your life, your mind. Forget again, and forget our daughter, and forget all that happened. Become a puppet again. Rest easily, and breathe so long as He allows you to, so long as you amuse Him. Kill me." 
<br />

<br />
Her whole body slowly began to shake, the memories drowning her deep in their depths. "I have nau choice, I have tried to escape before and failed. I have tried to break the tie and failed." Her hands trembled so violently she almost couldn't grasp the knife the priest handed her, his amusement at the scene palpable.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
