				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">The little girl patted her cheek. "Ilhar... mommy! Wake up, mommy! Someone is knocking at the door!" Eve stirred slowly, then snapped awake as the sound of mailed fists pounding worked its way into her consciousness. What the vith..? 
<br />

<br />
Picking up the five year old, and holding her on one hip, she moved towards the door, peering out. The Spire guard? What had happened.. She threw the door open, cradling the child. 
<br />

<br />
"What is it? What is wrong?" 
<br />

<br />
The head guard just looked at her, a hard expression in his eyes. "We have been sent for the child. She is to come with us now." 
<br />

<br />
"Wha.. why?" Eve looked at him in confusion. This was a man she saw every day when she brought Kieryn to the Spires. She had baked him food, and shared gossip and jokes. Why was he acting so cold? "Let me get us both dressed, and I will bring her." 
<br />

<br />
Rough hands reached for the child, pulling her out of her mother's grasp. "Nau, we come for her, naut you. She belongs to the Spires now, you have done your duty." Nodding to the other guards, he began to walk off with Kieryn, while the others barred Eve's way. The child started to cry, screaming for her mother. The woman in the doorway fought with all her strength, screaming her daughter's name. One of the guards looked at her, something approaching pity in his eyes, then turned his face away. Once the screams of the little one could no longer be heard, they stepped back and let her go. 
<br />

<br />
When the rough hands holding her released, Eve dropped in a heap to the ground, staring up at them, dazed and shaken. 
<br />

<br />
"Evileene Mahadrel, you will nau longer be allowed into the Spires. Your Hate has been measured, and found lacking. You will naut be allowed to infect the Child with your weakness. Do naut attempt to take her back, it will naut go well." 
<br />

<br />
The tormented woman watched them walk away, the strength finally coming back to her legs. Whimpering like a whipped puppy, she walked slowly to the Third Gate, moving as if she had numbered two thousand years, rather than her two hundred. As she approached the Spires, the screams of her daughter once again became audible, and forgetting everything, including the warning she was given, she ran for the entrance, intent on saving her little girl. A guard stepped in front of her, then another, staves at the ready. There was pain, much pain.. then nothing... </span>
<br />

<br />
"Touching, Ilharess. Very touching, but I grow bored. Finish it." 
<br />

<br />
The shaking stopped, a sudden strength of purpose coming over the woman standing there, torn in half. Over and over she had lost, with Innoruuk at the center of each tragedy, Innoruuk the cause. And now he would make her a murderer? Make her kill one that was helpless, make her break the Commandments she had lived for? But then, what was one more loss? The dagger was raised high, its blade already stained with blood, and slashed quickly and efficiently through its target. The ropes binding Zak's arms landed at his feet, the man moving with lightning quickness, grabbing the weapon of the guard next to him and swinging it with all the grace and skill she remembered. "You will die, Zak, but you will die free... as am I." Chaos erupted around them his blade swinging around, doing the most damage he could inflict, already wounds slashing red all over his body.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
