				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Eve started to speak the words that would gate her safely out of the Church, pausing briefly to look at Zak, and realizing it was too late.  She gated to another area of the Third Gate, near the forge that she had used so often, and then knelt down, pulling a small and ornate coffin from her packs. A few mystic words murmured, and she was holding her husband's bloody and lifeless corpse, her head bowed for a moment in grief, then steely resolution filling her eyes. She kissed his forehead, brushing his hair back from his face one last time. <span style="font-style: italic">Goodbye, Zak... may you find your peace.</span> Letting go of him she stood, ignoring the blood and gore that now covered the ill fitting robe she wore. She took a few steps forward and she was there, in a small, rarely used chapel, one that only those in V'Umbra had ever really used. Back to the beginning.. 
<br />

<br />
"I passed your test, Father! He is dead... and I killed him. Oh, naut with my own hands, but I knew what the result would be, and so did you." Her voice shook with anger and despair. "They brought him to me bound and helpless. I am NAUT a murderer. I do your will but I am naut a monster." Her fingernails dug into her palms as she shouted at the altar, willing Him to answer. "What of your Commandments, Father? What of them? Thou shall naut raise hand, word or sword against another tier'dal! Your priests demand we break those commandments, and for what? To prove our loyalty? I have bled for you, I have fought for you! I have lost everything I care about... FOR YOU! Over and over I have sacrificed. I am only what you made me. That is all I can be! When will it be enough? If I am soft, if I am too gentle, if I care too deeply, then look to Yourself for blame. I am Your Child, Your Creation. I know that You hold the power over my life. I know that Free Will is naut mine. But I can only be who You made me, naut someone else. If that is naut enough, take this life now and be done with it." Her shoulders sagged forward, her bloodstained hands reaching up to wipe tears she had not realized she was crying. "Thy Will be done."<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
