				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Eve stumbled back away from the altar, her shoulders bent in despair, but not completely bowed. There was still pride in her bearing, or perhaps it was that there was AGAIN pride in her bearing, she who had finally given up not long ago. Her spine straightened, showing a sense of purpose again. If she had been the kind that could summon fires and lightning bolts she would have, in her Hate. "Why should I expect YOU to answer, you have never answered. Ever the puppetmaster, and all of us your loyal brainless puppets. Did I fail, just because I did naut perform this task as you wished? The job was still finished, and I knew the outcome! I am guilty too. But because I could naut change my nature, did I fail? You do naut want children, you want dolls. Living, moving, unthinking DOLLS. I am nau doll, I am tier'dal. I breathe. I feel. I HATE. My Hatred is strong now, you should be proud.." For the first time she seemed to notice the gore covering her. She stripped off her robe, ignoring the fact that there was nothing underneath it. She walked, slowly, purposefully, without shame to the river that ran all through Neriak, and waded in, cleansing her body from the filth, though she feared her soul would never be clean. In the corner of her mind, she noticed a young jalil watching her, but could not bring herself to speak, not yet. 
<br />

<br />
A voice came from behind her, soft and low.  An old friend, a lover, an enemy and a confidante, all rolled into one.  Somehow the two of them could never get completely untangled from each other, and she was not surprised he was here.  Looking down at her he spoke slowly, "Eve... what can i do?"
<br />

<br />
She just watched him mutely, her eyes black pools in her face.  "I can help you forget Eve.  You have little respect for my tricks of the mind, I know, but I can ease your pain."<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
