				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">She glared at him, ebony eyes still shining with unshed tears. "You forget yourself, faern. And you forget who you speak to." Rather than cross her arms to hide her nudity, she stands proudly, arms akimbo. "I do naut want to lose my sadness, or my pain. It makes me who I am, and it is a tribute to those who have been lost. If I let it go, I am tarnishing their memory."
<br />

<br />
She looks at him, as if seeing him for the first time. "I belong here, Alger. I belong to Innoruuk, and I accept that. I hate Him with every fiber of my being, and that is how it should be. And I am hurt and I am tested, and that is how things are. You do naut belong here, abbil. You are naut truly one of His Children. You have naut been twisted by this Hate yet. Leave while you still can."
<br />

<br />
She turns around, wading deeper into the water, slowly, gracefully. With water to her shoulders, she pauses and looks back at him, her short white locks slicked back against her head, tears washed clean from her face. "You and Zaknyfein would have been friends, I think. He believed like you did, that there was something else for us. And he never let the Hate touch him. His body lies in the chapel nearby. Please take him, and perhaps have someone say a few words over him before you dispose of his corpse? I will naut raise that one again for Innoruuk's purpose. He deserves to be free of it all now, at least." A small smile curves her lips as she watches him for a moment, then swims deeper, turning over on her back to float, and staring up at the mystic images that glowed throughout the air, effectively dismissing him. Her eyes were dry now, and clear.
<br />

<br />
She noticed movement in the shadowy area of the bank and saw a young jalil there that looked familiar...<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
