				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Approaching the shore, Eve smiled down at the jalil, the curve of her mouth twisted slightly, as if the effort to smile cost her. "Vendui' dalharil. I hope that we did naut discomfit you. I assure you, I am naut the lunatic I might seem today."  The tier'dal girl looked up at her, the familiarity striking her even more.  She knew this child somehow... her name... Jhinrae, xas, that was it.  She stepped closer, a breath away from the jalil now.
<br />

<br />
Her hand threaded through the girl's ebony locks almost unconsciously, a faraway look in her eyes. "So young, so innocent. Do naut stay that way too long, dalharil. All those illusions.. the longer you believe, the more it hurts when they are revealed, and the more He holds you. Tis better.. or at least easier.. to be old, cynical, and heartless."
<br />

<br />
She reached up and ripped a cloth flag off of a sign pole, some sort of advertisement for one of the local shops. Wrapping it around herself, she walks away from the water, her shoulders stiff and proud, her bearing regal. Jhinrae had to strain to hear what she said as she walked towards the Hall of the Dead. "I forget that far too often..." 
<br />

<br />
Jhinrae called after her, stopping her in her tracks.  "Why do you feel such scorn for the Father, and why does he punish you as such, Mistress?"  She flushed slightly.  "I overheard you in the Chapel, and then followed you here.  I am naut sure why, I am naut usually the type to eavesdrop.."
<br />

<br />
Eve stopped where she was standing, and sat down on the stone path, patting the spot next to her. This one was curious, to be sure, and still so naive in the ways of her people. A laugh bubbled out from her throat, low and musical. "Naut in your nature, dalharil? Why of course it is, you're tier'dal. It's in your BLOOD." As the girl approached and sat down, Eve reached out and smoothed a piece of hair back from Jhinrae's face, caressing her cheek in an almost motherly manner.
<br />

<br />
"You do know the story of our creation, dalharil? Of how the original king and queen of the elves were kidnapped by the Father? Of how for hundreds of years He tortured them, mentally and physically, excrutiating pain, until He had twisted them into what we are today. The 'perfect' tier'dal." Her mouth twisted bitterly. "He tortures even His most devout followers. That is His nature. He feeds on Hatred, even ours for Him." Absently, she starts finger combing the girl's hair, taken back to the times of having her own child.
<br />

<br />
"That is naut to say I do naut follow him, dalharil, for I do. He is my Father, and I am His Living Will. But He wants my Hatred and yours as much as He wants the Hatred of the Others. I have lost two... well, three... daughters, and my husband to His Will. I have died for His Will. I have been raised for His Will."<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
