			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"I know of Kerath, but I only know of one daughter, Lierin..."
<br />

<br />
Eve smiles sadly. "Naut many know of her. Fewer know that Kerath is her father. Lierin only found out after my death, perhaps that is part of what sent her over the edge of sanity..."
<br />

<br />
She looked at the girl, her eyes searching, as if to be sure Jhinrae was prepared to hear the rest of her story. "I didn't raise Kieryn in the tier'dal tradition. She was raised by me. Actually, all of my qu'ellar helped, she was an adorable child and they all watched out for her and watched her grow. When she was perhaps five years old, the guards of the Spires came to my door, and they said they were there for Kieryn. That was normal, there had been a prophesy that she would be able to do something nau other tier'dal had ever done, what that was nau one knew. The Oracle as usual was vague. But the Spires watched her closely because of that."
<br />

<br />
Her eyes dropped to the ground, remembered pain dulling her eyes. Her long, slender indigo-skinned fingers knotted together awkwardly, her hands shifting in distress. Her toes curled, pulling back under the cloth she was draped in, as if she was trying to pull back into herself. "That day was different however. The guards, jaluken I had talked to, joked with, even baked for, they said I was naut welcome to come with her. That I was naut going to see Kieryn again. That my faith had been judged and found lacking. That my Hate was false..." She licked suddenly dry lips. "When I ran after them, I heard my daughter screaming for me, then the guards blocked my path. They.. they beat me into unconsciousness, and left me there. I never saw Kieryn again. I left Neriak soon after." She glanced off in the distance, her eyes closed briefly, then opened again, carefully blank of all emotion. 
<br />

<br />
"I had fought so hard against the Kindred and the vampires. There was a day in Nektulos when Syriux, Hallistra and myself challenged them. Members of all three qu'ellars came to support us. Hallistra fought Aquaenus, the sire. I was particularly furious, for he had turned one of my abbilen, another tier'dal, into an abomination like himself. But that is a story for another day.. I had fought hard against them, yet I let them become a haven to me when I fled Neriak. I knew Aquaenus would take me in, for you see I had had private dealings with him as well, to my shame."
<br />

<br />
One hand raked through her short locks, setting them even more on end, the look wild and spikey. Her eyes too were wild, wide and dilated, her emotions obviously at the breaking point. She almost seemed to forget Jhinrae was there at times, just stumbling through her story, the words coming out in a jumble, a catharsis perhaps.
<br />

<br />
"And so I joined the Kindred, but I was naut turned. I refused to become a vampire. That would have been a betrayal of everything I knew. They let me hide away in a cabin, rather than the Keep, and I rarely saw or spoke to anyone. Lierin and Kerath's wife, Raevynne, came with me, but I shut them out as well."<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
